This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with image super-resolution using convolutional neural networks. The use of deep learning models and loss functions also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The mention of benchmark datasets and evaluations suggests that it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the use of transposed convolutions and resource-aware applications suggests that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category.
